6. omnia—desiderant; as in the case of Porcius Latro, x, 5, 18. actionem aqua deficit, the water faite, or oute off the speech. The reference is to the clepsydra, or water-clock, a small instrument which timed the speaker by the gradual run-' ning out of the drops of water, like the saud in an honr-glass. A certain number of clepsydrae was allowed the speaker in trials, whether in the senate or in the courts. Plin. Ep. ii, 11, 14: duodecim clepsydris, quas spatiosissimas acceperam, sumt ’ additae quatuor. loquendum.
